Double Happiness (French: Bonheur aigre-doux) is a 1994 film by Canadian director Mina Shum, co-produced by First Generations Films and the National Film Board of Canada.The film stars Sandra Oh as Jade Li, an artist struggling to assert her independence from the expectations of her Chinese Canadian family. Callum Keith Rennie also stars as Mark, Jade's love interest.Oh won the Genie Award for Best Performance by an Actress in a Leading Role for this film.